posts.name: Ian Bae
posts.cooked: G415 Expansion limits. A ROBOT may not extend more than 1 ft. 6 in. (~45 cm) beyond the vertical projection of its ROBOT PERIMETER. If the over-expansion is due to damage and not used for strategic benefit, it is an exception to this rule, and no penalty is imposed. Violation: MINOR FOUL, or MAJOR FOUL if the over-expansion is used for strategic benefit, including if it impedes or enables a scoring action.
